From 5e92216d824ff59d32ee82e18c55ada901efcf21 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 11:48:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 19/67] fix(macos): isolate engine behind an opaque bridge so
 ObjC++ compiles on GCC
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The engine headers cannot be included from an Objective-C++ translation unit:
vtbackend uses `id` as an ordinary identifier (Functions.h operator id_type()
returning id(), VTType/Charset `switch (id)`), which collides with the `id`
keyword under the ObjC++ frontend; gcc16's own <chrono> format header also fails
there. Both were pulled in transitively by TerminalView.mm including
TerminalSession.h -> Terminal.h.

Introduce SessionBridge.{h,cpp}: a thin, engine-free ABI (opaque
TerminalSession* handle + plain functions taking primitives) that the .mm files
call. SessionBridge.cpp is compiled as ordinary C++ and is the only place that
includes engine headers; TerminalView.mm/main.mm now include ONLY SessionBridge.h
+ TerminalView.h + AppKit — verified engine-header-free. Also: declare
ContourAppDelegate <NSApplicationDelegate>, cast the CGBitmapInfo enum-or to
uint32_t, and route object deletion through bridge_destroy() (GCC's ObjC++ parser
mis-reads `delete [self session]` as array-delete).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
